Looking for a quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our
Caribbean Style BBQ Beans in just 20-25 minutes for a delicious and speedy
meal.

== Rice ==

Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high
heat. Add the @Basmati Rice{150%grams} and cook for ~{10-12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{}
and leave to the side until ready to serve.

== Preparation ==

In the meantime, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}(peeled) (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{60%grams}.

Drain and rinse the @Mixed Beans{1%carton} in a sieve.

== Caribbean Style BBQ Beans ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the garlic, @Tomato Puree{30%grams} and
@Caribbean Style Jerk{2%sachets}. Fry for ~{1%min}.

Stir in the mixed beans, @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%grams},
@Sugar{1/2%tsp} and @Water for the Sauce{100%milliliters} (see pantry for both
amounts).

Bring to the boil, then lower to a simmer. Cook until thickened slightly,
~{3-4%mins}.

Meanwhile, halve the @Avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to
scoop the flesh out onto a #board{}, face-down.

Slice into 1cm thick slices.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once the sauce has thickened, add the @Baby Spinach{40%grams} to the pan a
handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}.

Remove from the heat, then stir in the @BBQ Sauce{48%grams} and @Butter{20%grams}
(see pantry for amount).

Taste, and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

== To Serve ==

Share the rice between your #serving bowls{}.

Top with your Caribbean style BBQ beans.

Sprinkle over the Cheddar and @Crispy Onions{1%sachet}.

Finish by fanning out the sliced avocado on top of each bowl.

Enjoy!